"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-26-paris-olympics-officially-underway-historic-opening-ceremony-kicks-off-games-21305746\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The ParisOlympicsis up and running after a spectacular - if soggy - opening ceremony kick-started what promises to be a fortnight of compelling action and drama.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 161, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ParisOlympicsis\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 19}, {\"ngram\": \"soggy - opening ceremony kick\", \"from\": 60, \"to\": 89}, {\"ngram\": \"a fortnight\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 129}, {\"ngram\": \"compelling action\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 150}, {\"ngram\": \"drama\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 160}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spectators had already been treated to plenty of memorable moments after the football, rugby sevens, handball and shooting competitions began in the week, but tonight'sParade of Nationsand the symbolic lighting of the torch marked the official start of the Games.\", \"from\": 163, \"to\": 426, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Spectators\", \"from\": 163, \"to\": 173}, {\"ngram\": \"plenty\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 208}, {\"ngram\": \"memorable moments\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 229}, {\"ngram\": \"the football\", \"from\": 236, \"to\": 248}, {\"ngram\": \"rugby\", \"from\": 250, \"to\": 255}, {\"ngram\": \"handball\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 272}, {\"ngram\": \"shooting competitions\", \"from\": 277, \"to\": 298}, {\"ngram\": \"the week\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 316}, {\"ngram\": \"Nationsand\", \"from\": 341, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"the symbolic lighting\", \"from\": 352, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"the torch\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 386}, {\"ngram\": \"the official start\", \"from\": 394, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 425}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first time in Olympic history, thissummer's opening ceremony - which kicked off the first Games in 100 years in the French capital - took place outside of the main athletics stadium.\", \"from\": 428, \"to\": 618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 552, \"end\": 558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.668340731392496, \"rank\": 0.49253828412170503, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 432, \"to\": 446}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic history\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 465}, {\"ngram\": \"thissummer's opening ceremony\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Games\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 531}, {\"ngram\": \"100 years\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 544}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 579}, {\"ngram\": \"the main athletics stadium\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the early evening, a fleet of boats began carrying sportsmen and women from the 206 competing nations down a 6km stretch of the River Seine ahead of the ambitious spectacle's crescendo at the Trocadero.\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 751, \"end\": 762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the early evening\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 640}, {\"ngram\": \"a fleet\", \"from\": 642, \"to\": 649}, {\"ngram\": \"boats\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 658}, {\"ngram\": \"sportsmen\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 683}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 693}, {\"ngram\": \"the 206 competing nations\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 724}, {\"ngram\": \"a 6km stretch\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 743}, {\"ngram\": \"the ambitious spectacle's crescendo\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"the Trocadero\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 824}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A series of co-ordinated arson attacks paralysed France's rail networkon the eve of the ceremony but it's believed as many as 600,000 fans flocked to the Olympics' epicentre to witness a piece of history.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 1031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 876, \"end\": 882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8412001552781928, \"rank\": 0.1879279439327713, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A series\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 835}, {\"ngram\": \"-ordinated arson attacks\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 865}, {\"ngram\": \"the eve\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 907}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 923}, {\"ngram\": \"as many as 600,000 fans\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 965}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics' epicentre\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1000}, {\"ngram\": \"a piece\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1019}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1030}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around 6,800 of the world's finest athletes took centre stage across the four-hour-long party, which Lady Gaga helped launch with a dazzling French cabaret performance of Renee Jeanmaire's 'Mon Truc en Plumes'.\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1134, \"end\": 1143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 1174, \"end\": 1180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.668340731392496, \"rank\": 0.49253828412170503, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world's finest athletes\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"centre stage\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1094}, {\"ngram\": \"the four-hour-long party\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1126}, {\"ngram\": \"Renee Jeanmaire's 'Mon Truc\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1231}, {\"ngram\": \"Plumes\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it was Canadian pop icon Celine Dionwho stole the show with a stunning public comeback to close the ceremony.\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1256, \"end\": 1264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9980080768935558, \"rank\": 0.0019958472240020173, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1303}, {\"ngram\": \"a stunning public comeback\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1357}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Parade of Nations departed from the Pont d'Austerlitz and came to a halt at the Pont d'Iena, before a grand finale - set against the unmistakable backdrop of the Eiffel Tower - brought the ceremony to an end.\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1572, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Parade\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1370}, {\"ngram\": \"Nations\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pont d'Austerlitz\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1417}, {\"ngram\": \"a halt\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1436}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pont d'Iena\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1455}, {\"ngram\": \"a grand finale\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1478}, {\"ngram\": \"the unmistakable backdrop\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1518}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1538}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1561}, {\"ngram\": \"an end\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1571}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This summer, each and every one of the medals, whether bronze, silver or gold, will contain a unique piece of iron from the iconic landmark.\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1714, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1635}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1637, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1647, \"to\": 1651}, {\"ngram\": \"a unique piece\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1680}, {\"ngram\": \"iron\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1688}, {\"ngram\": \"the iconic landmark\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1713}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As is tradition, Greece were the first nation to enter the Parade of Nations and Team GB, led by flagbearers Tom Daley and Helen Glover, appeared in 72nd place.\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1733, \"end\": 1739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.999625746956056, \"rank\": 0.00036842979397184083, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1797, \"end\": 1804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999080105269, \"rank\": 9.100477532441597e-08, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.113735976044381e-39, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}, {\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"tradition\", \"from\": 1722, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"the first nation\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1761}, {\"ngram\": \"the Parade\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1781}, {\"ngram\": \"Nations\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1792}, {\"ngram\": \"72nd place\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 1875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competing at his fifth Games since Beijing, gold-medal winning diver Daley revealed it was a 'dream come true' to be given the honour of flying the flag for Great Britain and Northern Ireland.\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 2070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1913, \"end\": 1920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999988572199, \"rank\": 1.1429599609965154e-09, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2035, \"end\": 2048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999995452526, \"rank\": 2.9985213375630743e-10, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2053, \"end\": 2069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999997438463071, \"rank\": 2.56153554208177e-07, \"text\": \"Northern Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his fifth Games\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 1906}, {\"ngram\": \"gold-medal winning diver Daley\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"a 'dream\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1977}, {\"ngram\": \"the honour\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2011}, {\"ngram\": \"the flag\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2030}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Legendary British rower Glover, meanwhile, said: 'I never thought I would be an Olympian!\", \"from\": 2072, \"to\": 2161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2152, \"end\": 2160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.999999995408416, \"rank\": 4.591472009844791e-09, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Glover\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2102}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being part of history as a flagbearer, I have not really got my head round it yet.\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2244, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2168, \"to\": 2172}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2183}, {\"ngram\": \"a flagbearer\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2199}, {\"ngram\": \"my head\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2230}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Everyone I have told so far has cried, and I cried when I was told, which goes to show how much of an honour it is and how much it means.'\", \"from\": 2246, \"to\": 2385, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Everyone\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2255}, {\"ngram\": \"an honour\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2355}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among those on board the Team GB boat was Andy Murray, who said he was relishing the opportunity to soak up the atmosphere of an opening ceremony ahead of his last ever tennis tournament.\", \"from\": 2387, \"to\": 2574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2412, \"end\": 2419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999080105269, \"rank\": 9.100477532441597e-08, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2429, \"end\": 2440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.22910702564878e-38, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \